&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AffirmedRx&lt;/strong&gt; is on a mission to improve health care outcomes by bringing clarity, integrity, and trust to pharmacy benefit management. We are committed to making pharmacy benefits easy to understand, straightforward to access and always in the best interest of employers and the lives they impact. We accomplish this by bringing total clarity to business practices, leading with clinical approaches, and utilizing state-of-the-art technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us in improving health care outcomes for all!&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;We promise to do what’s right, always.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AVP, Formulary&amp;nbsp;Strategy&amp;nbsp;is a senior clinical and strategic leader responsible for the vision, architecture, and long-term integrity of&amp;nbsp;AffirmedRx’s&amp;nbsp;formulary program. Reporting to the VP of Clinical &amp;amp; Specialty Strategies, this role serves as the enterprise-level owner of formulary design, governance, and market positioning, translating clinical evidence, rebate dynamics, and client financial goals into a coherent,&amp;nbsp;clinically&amp;nbsp;and financially sound formulary&amp;nbsp;strategy. The AVP operates at the intersection of clinical rigor and business&amp;nbsp;impact and&amp;nbsp;is expected to lead, influencing across the organization through&amp;nbsp;expertise, judgment, and collaborative leadership.&amp;nbsp;As the function grows, the AVP will&amp;nbsp;also&amp;nbsp;shape the&amp;nbsp;team&amp;nbsp;structure and talent strategy needed to scale formulary operations across a growing client portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formulary Strategy and Architecture: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and evolve the organization’s formulary strategy, including multi-tier architecture, therapeutic category management, biosimilar positioning, and specialty drug&amp;nbsp;placement ensuring&amp;nbsp;alignment with net-cost principles and&amp;nbsp;AffirmedRx’s&amp;nbsp;transparent PBM model&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead enterprise-level evaluation and ongoing governance of formulary tier structures, ensuring clinical defensibility, rebate alignment, and consistency with client value propositions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;cost thresholds, tier placement logic, and formulary decision criteria that can be applied consistently across the client portfolio&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Rebate Strategy and Account Management to align formulary architecture with rebate contract performance and client financial objectives&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead formulary pipeline monitoring and serve as the internal expert on drug approvals, biosimilar transitions, specialty pipeline developments, and market shifts with formulary implications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Governance and P&amp;amp;T Oversight:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a strategic partner to the P&amp;amp;T Committee, ensuring formulary decisions are evidence-based, properly documented, and communicated in compliance with applicable regulatory requirements&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the development of clinical monographs, formulary recommendation summaries, and therapeutic review materials for P&amp;amp;T review cycles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;clinical review standards that govern how new molecular entities, biosimilars, and specialty products are evaluated for formulary inclusion&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and assess clinical literature and AMCP dossiers to guide formulary positioning and support coverage policy development&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
